# /backfill handler

When the user types `/backfill` in chat:

1. Scan the last 30–50 turns of the current conversation.
2. Identify skill-shaped capture candidates using these signals:
   - User said "actually", "no", "instead", "next time", "never", "always" (HIGH)
   - Same topic corrected twice (HIGH)
   - Agent violated a rule already in context (HIGH)
   - User narrated a workaround (MEDIUM)
   - User pushed back then accepted new approach (MEDIUM)
   - Style preference signal (LOW)
3. Present up to 5 candidates as a numbered list with confidence tags and source turn references.
4. Ask: `Accept? [all | none | 1,2 | edit N: <revision>]`
5. For accepted candidates, invoke `/remember` for each (via `.skills/remember.sh` or `gh api` fallback).
6. Report each result on its own line.

## Rules
- Never auto-persist. Always show candidates first, wait for user choice.
- Max 5 candidates. Top by confidence.
- Skip candidates that duplicate skills already captured in this session.
- If user rejects a candidate, do not resurface it in this session.

## This is a manual command in v1
Auto-invoke at session end is Phase 1.5.
